messages.messageBody:
In a message dated 3/7/02 3:19:57 PM Central Standard Time,
AlwaysLearning@yahoogroups.com writes:

<< For those of you in small states, just because New Mexico and Texas touch
doesn't mean we can zip over there for the weekend very easily. I could
drive four hours in any direction and still be in New Mexico (six or seven
in
some directions). >>

Ha, ha....try ALASKA sometime!!
7-8 hours to get to another actual city isn't that long. Of course there are
only two places I would actually call a "city"...the rest are basically
villages or towns.

I do Pensacola to Jonesboro, TN in one day usually (past Knoxville) which is
about 11 hours of driving. So I just assume other people are just as insane.
It's a lot more fun to split it up and take it easy.

Welcome to the list Cris! Good to hear from the other Kenski.

Is the information out on the price and hotel accomodations for the SC
conference? I haven't gotten any details yet.

Ren
